Unknown gunmen have kidnapped an Anglican cleric, Venerable Olu Obanla along Ifon-Okeluse road in Ose local government rea of Ondo State.  The cleric, according to a source, was abducted by the gunmen alongside his son on Saturday evening.  LEADERSHIP gathered that the victims were travelling along the road when the hoodlums accosted and dragged them into the bush to an unknown destination.  The source further informed that shortly after the abduction, the kidnappers contacted the family and demanded a sum of N10million for the release of the victims.  The family was unable to raise the money as they could only gather N1million which was rejected by the abductors.  The source said, “Venerable Olu Obanla and his son were kidnapped yesterday (Saturday) on their way to Okeluse in Ondo State.  “The kidnappers have contacted the family and ransom of N10million was demanded by the kidnappers but the family raised only N1million but the kidnappers rejected it.”  Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer, Ondo Polics Command, Mrs Funmilayo Odunlami, said efforts were ongoing by the detectives of the command to rescue the victims.